The approach is sometimes referred to as [[megavitamin therapy]]<ref name="isbn1-59120-226-4"/><ref name="pmid7207301"/> as the practice evolved out of, and in some cases still uses, doses of [[vitamin]]s and [[Dietary mineral|minerals]] many times higher than the recommended [[Dietary Reference Intake]]. Orthomolecular practitioners may also incorporate a variety of other treatment modalities into their approaches, including [[Diet (nutrition)|dietary]] restriction, megadoses of non-vitamin nutrients, and mainstream [[pharmaceutical drugs]].<ref name="isbn1-59120-226-4" /><ref name="Braverman">
{{cite journal
|author=Braverman Eric
|title=Orthomolecular Medicine and Megavitamin Therapy: Future and Philosophy
