}}</ref> According to Hoffer and others who called themselves "orthomolecular psychiatrists", psychiatric syndromes result from biochemical deficiencies, allergies, toxicities or several hypothetical contributing conditions which they termed [[Orthomolecular psychiatry#Pyroluria|pyroluria]], [[Orthomolecular psychiatry#Histadelia|histadelia]] and [[Orthomolecular psychiatry#Histapenia|histapenia]]. These purported causes were said to be found during an "individual biochemical workup" and treated with [[megavitamin therapy]] and dietary changes including [[fasting]].<ref name=Edelman>
